     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>READER.</head>
   <l>THis Crystall sight is not for all mens Eyes,</l>
   <l>But onely serues for the iudicious wise,</l>
   <l>Fooles, they may gaze as long as ere they will,</l>
   <l>And be as blind as any Beetle still:</l>
   <l>A purblinde <hi>Momus</hi> fleeringly will looke,</l>
   <l>And spie no knaue but's selfe in all the Booke.</l>
   <l>A <hi>Sicophant,</hi> that slaues himselfe to all,</l>
   <l>Will his owne Knaue-Companions honest call,</l>
   <l>And wilfull winke, because he will not see,</l>
   <l>With diuers sorts of Buzzards else that be:</l>
   <l>But these we leaue to their defectiue sight,</l>
   <l>With Bats and Owles that blinded are by light.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>S. R.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
